front office careeredit weary of the lifestyle of a minor league player beane approached athletics gm sandy alderson a day after he was reassigned to minor league camp in april  and asked for a job as an advance scout beane held this position through  when he was promoted to assistant gm of the athletics tasked with scouting minor league players under the ownership of walter a haas jr the athletics appeared in three consecutive world series from  through  and had the highest payroll in baseball in  haas died in  and new owners stephen schott and ken hofmann ordered alderson to slash payroll to field a competitive roster on a limited budget alderson began focusing on sabermetric principles to obtain relatively undervalued players he valued onbase percentage among hitters alderson taught beane to find value that other teams did not see using sabermetrics beane succeeded alderson as gm on october   he continued aldersons crafting of the athletics into one of the most costeffective teams in baseball for example in the  mlb season the athletics ranked th of  major league teams in player salaries but had the thbest regularseason record beane left at the  toronto international film festival the athletics reached the playoffs in four consecutive years from  through  losing in the american league division series each year in  the athletics became the first team in the  plus years of american league baseball to win  consecutive games they won their first playoff series under beane in  when they swept the minnesota twins in the american league division series but were subsequently swept by the detroit tigers in the american league championship series other low payroll teams such as the  world champion florida marlins and the  american league champion tampa bay rays have appeared in the world series with the former going on to win the world series in  its all about evaluating skills and putting a price on them thirty years ago stockbrokers used to buy stock strictly by feel lets put it this way anyone in the game with a k has a choice they can choose a fund manager who manages their retirement by gut instinct or one who chooses by research and analysis i know which way id choose –billy beane after the  season the boston red sox made beane an offer of  to become their gm but he declined on april   beane received a contract extension to remain with the athletics as its general manager through  and new team owner lewis wolff awarded beane a small portion of the teams ownership in february  the athletics extended beanes contract through  from their  playoff appearance until  when they again made the playoffs the athletics had not made the playoffs or finished above  which had triggered criticism of beane and his approach in some quarters in baseball especially in  beane largely dismisses criticism of his approach indicating that his philosophy revolves around research and analysis many other general managers have followed beanes strategy and now use similar approaches the book itself has changed the way different players are valued and beane began concentrating on high school players a group he once largely ignored in the mlb draft considering them to be heavily undervalued he and other likeminded gms also changed their draft strategies to focus more on defensive skills which had become undervalued in the years immediately after the moneyball revolution this new emphasis on defense was displayed in the  season although the athletics finished at  and again missed the playoffs they led mlb in defensive efficiency measured as the percentage of balls put into play by opponents that resulted in outs and allowed the fewest runs in the al in the  season the athletics again made the playoffs under beane winning the american league west title on the last day of the regular season the athletics returned to the playoffs in  by also winning the american league west division title in the  season the teams first backtoback division championships since the – seasons in december  sports illustrated named beane as number  on its list of the top  gmsexecutives of the decade in all sportsa on october   the oakland athletics announced that beane had been promoted to executive vice president of baseball operations assistant gm david forst assumed the job of general manager activities outside baseballedit socceredit when the athletics ownership group agreed to purchase the reincarnation of the san jose earthquakes of major league soccer beane who has expressed a passion for soccer began developing a system for objectively analyzing soccer players he has agreed to help the earthquakes front office develop a method for building a costeffective team as the salary cap in mls is even more restrictive than the athletics status as a smallmarket team in major league baseball however a system has yet to be implemented beane has claimed that arsenal manager arsène wenger is a personal idol his friendship with exarsenal scout damien comolli and arsenal owner stan kroenke allowed him to delve deep into the world of english football in march  the dutch football club az alkmaar under general director robert eenhoorn a former major leaguer hired beane as an advisor software industryedit on january   the software company netsuite named beane to its board of directors netsuite cofounder evan goldberg cited beanes ability to combine facts with instinct as an important factor in the decision to involve him in the company beane also served as a consultant for and also appears in the video game mlb front office manager depiction in book and film moneyballedit because of his teams success despite its low payroll beane was the subject of author michael lewiss  bestselling book moneyball the art of winning an unfair game the book discusses beanes methods as the gm of the athletics and how he along with harvardeducated statistician paul depodesta used sabermetric principles to run his team in a costeffective way according to the book this allowed him to be successful despite his financial constraints the book and beanes methods have influenced the way many think about the game of baseball including other teams and players brad pitt played the role of beane in the  film moneyball pitt was nominated for the  academy award for best actor in a leading role for his performance personal lifeedit twice married beane has a daughter casey from his first marriage and twins brayden and tinsley from his current marriage he attended the university of california san diego during the baseball offseasons of his playing career notesedit  the lists only other mlb executives were theo epstein no  and pat gillick no  referencesedit biography portal baseball portal bibliography lewis michael d  moneyball the art of winning an unfair game new york w w norton isbn   inline citations  a b c d e moneyball p    oakland as executive profiles billy beane mlbmlbcom october   retrieved june     moneyball p    a b moneyball p    a b moneyball p    mets get first grab the bonham daily favorite united press international june   p  retrieved august     moneyball pp –   moneyball p    moneyball pp –   moneyball p    a b moneyball p    moneyball p    moneyball pp –   twins trade tim teufel the michigan daily associated press january   p  retrieved march     mets trade for twins teufel stadler mize share hope lead sun sentinel january   p c retrieved march   subscription required help   beanes battle minneapolis star tribune march   retrieved march   subscription required help   a b hafner dan september   american league roundup expanded roster gives twins a quick payoff los angeles times p  retrieved march   subscription required help   twins deal for gladden drop hatcher sample minneapolis startribune april   retrieved march   subscription required help   puckett homer could spur pennant drive minneapolis startribune september   retrieved march   subscription required help   expos buy pinchhitter nettles philadelphia daily news march   retrieve